== Ubuntu ==
 * Package format: .deb
 * Packages:
  * http://packages.ubuntu.com/
  * https://launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/$PACKAGE for source packages
 * BTS: http://bugs.launchpad.net/ubuntu
 * VCS: sometimes you have to consider the VCS used by the Debian developer and a VCS used by a MOTU (usually http://code.launchpad.net/ubuntu )
 * Changes: same format as Debian
 * Wiki: http://wiki.ubuntu.com
 * Translations: http://translations.launchpad.net/ubuntu
 * Feature requests: http://brainstorm.ubuntu.com/
 * Blueprints (feature specifications tracker): http://blueprints.launchpad.net/ubuntu
 * CVE: https://launchpad.net/bugs/cve/$CVE
 * CVE: http://people.canonical.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/$CVE
== Yoper ==
 * Package format: rpm
 * Packages: http://development.yoper.com/pub/devel/source-cache/
 * Package QA:
  * http://www.yoper.com/wiki
  * http://www.yoper.com/forum/
 * BTS: http://www.yoper.com/bugtracker
 * Changes: Automatic, through build server history checkins
 * patches: Hardly any patches, one of he principles of Yoper. Back to the source and optimised for the purpose.
 * VCSes: svn+ssh://development.yoper.com/thinktank
 * Homepage: http:/www.yoper.com

